description:
&lt;p&gt;Are you a friendly, motivated and enthusiastic Band 5 nurse looking for a role that provides exposure to wide ranging learning and development opportunities? If so then the dynamic and supportive team within Neurosciences at the Queen Elizabeth Hospital Birmingham is for you.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Ward 409 at the Queen Elizabeth Hospital cares for neurosurgical patients, giving you the fantastic opportunity to enhance and develop your clinical skills and knowledge in caring for patients with neurological conditions.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We work collaboratively with other disciplines including the nutrition team, tissue viability, therapists and specialist nurses, providing you with excellent opportunities for career development and to enhance your knowledge and skills.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will be given the opportunity to undertake a range of in house training days, attend externally run conferences, post graduate study as well as learning new clinical skills to support you in your role. The supportive team and dedicated clinical educator will strive to help you achieve your developmental goals.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For more information on the role or if would like to arrange an informal visit please contact Nathan.Williams@uhb.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
